      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "One-Step Look-Ahead"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The simplest interleaved form: plan exactly one step, execute it, observe the result, then plan the next step. The LLM receives the accumulated execution history \u2014 completed steps and their results \u2014 as context for each planning call."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass StepRecord:\n    description: str\n    tool: str\n    tool_input: dict\n    result: Optional[Any] = None\n\nONE_STEP_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are planning the next single step for an agent.\n\nGoal: {goal}\n\nSteps completed so far:\n{history}\n\nWhat is the single next action needed? If the goal is complete, respond with:\n  {{\"done\": true}}\nOtherwise respond with:\n  {{\"description\": str, \"tool\": str, \"tool_input\": dict}}\n\"\"\"\n\ndef plan_next_step(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    goal: str,\n    history: list[StepRecord],\n) -> Optional[StepRecord]:\n    hist_text = \"\\n\".join(\n        f\"  {i+1}. {s.description} \u2192 {s.result}\"\n        for i, s in enumerate(history)\n    ) or \"  (none)\"\n    prompt = ONE_STEP_PROMPT.format(goal=goal, history=hist_text)\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":prompt}],\n    )\n    import json, re\n    raw = resp.content[0].text\n    m = re.search(r\"\\{.*\\}\", raw, re.DOTALL)\n    if not m:\n        return None\n    data = json.loads(m.group())\n    if data.get(\"done\"):\n        return None\n    return StepRecord(\n        description=data[\"description\"],\n        tool=data[\"tool\"],\n        tool_input=data[\"tool_input\"],\n    )\n\n\ndef run_interleaved(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    goal: str,\n    execute_fn,\n    max_steps: int = 20,\n) -> list[StepRecord]:\n    history: list[StepRecord] = []\n    for _ in range(max_steps):\n        step = plan_next_step(client, goal, history)\n        if step is None:\n            break   # planner says we're done\n        step.result = execute_fn(step)\n        history.append(step)\n    return history\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The max_steps guard prevents infinite loops if the planner never signals completion. Twenty steps covers most agentic tasks; adjust based on task complexity."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "K-Step Look-Ahead"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "One-step look-ahead is the most responsive but most expensive variant \u2014 one planning LLM call per step. K-step look-ahead balances efficiency and adaptability: plan K steps at a time, execute them, then re-plan the next K using updated context."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "K_STEP_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are planning the next {k} steps for an agent.\n\nGoal: {goal}\n\nSteps completed so far:\n{history}\n\nGenerate exactly {k} steps (or fewer if the goal will complete sooner).\nRespond with JSON array:\n[{{\"description\": str, \"tool\": str, \"tool_input\": dict}}]\nIf the goal is already complete, return [].\n\"\"\"\n\ndef plan_k_steps(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    goal: str,\n    history: list[StepRecord],\n    k: int = 3,\n) -> list[StepRecord]:\n    hist_text = \"\\n\".join(\n        f\"  {i+1}. {s.description} \u2192 {s.result}\"\n        for i, s in enumerate(history)\n    ) or \"  (none)\"\n    prompt = K_STEP_PROMPT.format(goal=goal, history=hist_text, k=k)\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":prompt}],\n    )\n    import json, re\n    raw = resp.content[0].text\n    m = re.search(r\"\\[.*\\]\", raw, re.DOTALL)\n    if not m:\n        return []\n    data = json.loads(m.group())\n    return [\n        StepRecord(description=s[\"description\"], tool=s[\"tool\"], tool_input=s[\"tool_input\"])\n        for s in data\n    ]\n\n\ndef run_k_step_interleaved(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    goal: str,\n    execute_fn,\n    k: int = 3,\n    max_steps: int = 30,\n) -> list[StepRecord]:\n    history: list[StepRecord] = []\n    while len(history) < max_steps:\n        batch = plan_k_steps(client, goal, history, k)\n        if not batch:\n            break\n        for step in batch:\n            step.result = execute_fn(step)\n            history.append(step)\n    return history\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "With k=3, the agent plans three steps, executes all three, then re-plans. This cuts planning LLM calls by a factor of k compared to one-step look-ahead while still adapting every k steps rather than committing the entire plan upfront."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Observation-Gated Re-Planning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rather than re-planning on a fixed interval, observation-gated re-planning only calls the planner when the last step's result is surprising \u2014 when it differs significantly from the expected outcome. Routine results proceed without a planning call; only deviations trigger a fresh look."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "SURPRISE_PROMPT = \"\"\"Did this step produce a surprising result?\n\nExpected outcome: {expected}\nActual result: {actual}\n\nRespond with JSON: {{\"surprising\": true/false, \"reason\": str}}\n\"\"\"\n\ndef is_surprising(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    expected: str,\n    actual: Any,\n) -> bool:\n    prompt = SURPRISE_PROMPT.format(expected=expected, actual=str(actual)[:500])\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=128,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":prompt}],\n    )\n    import json, re\n    raw = resp.content[0].text\n    m = re.search(r\"\\{.*\\}\", raw, re.DOTALL)\n    if not m:\n        return False\n    return json.loads(m.group()).get(\"surprising\", False)\n\n\ndef run_observation_gated(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    goal: str,\n    execute_fn,\n    k: int = 3,\n    max_steps: int = 30,\n) -> list[StepRecord]:\n    history: list[StepRecord] = []\n    pending: list[StepRecord] = []\n    while len(history) < max_steps:\n        if not pending:\n            pending = plan_k_steps(client, goal, history, k)\n        if not pending:\n            break\n        step = pending.pop(0)\n        step.result = execute_fn(step)\n        history.append(step)\n        if is_surprising(client, step.description, step.result):\n            pending = []   # discard remaining look-ahead; re-plan next iteration\n    return history\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a result is surprising, pending is cleared and the while loop re-plans from scratch on the next iteration. When results are routine, the pre-planned batch executes without additional planning calls \u2014 saving tokens on predictable sub-tasks."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "History Window Management"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "As execution continues, the history passed to the planner grows. A 30-step history with verbose results can easily exceed the context window or inflate planning costs. Summarisation compresses old history into a short digest while keeping recent steps verbatim."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "SUMMARISE_PROMPT = \"\"\"Summarise the following completed steps for an agent.\nGoal: {goal}\nSteps:\n{steps}\nProduce a 2-3 sentence summary of what has been accomplished and what is now known.\n\"\"\"\n\ndef compress_history(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    goal: str,\n    history: list[StepRecord],\n    keep_recent: int = 5,\n) -> list[StepRecord]:\n    if len(history) <= keep_recent:\n        return history\n    old = history[:-keep_recent]\n    recent = history[-keep_recent:]\n    steps_text = \"\\n\".join(\n        f\"  {i+1}. {s.description} \u2192 {s.result}\" for i, s in enumerate(old)\n    )\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=256,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\n            SUMMARISE_PROMPT.format(goal=goal, steps=steps_text)}],\n    )\n    summary_text = resp.content[0].text.strip()\n    summary_step = StepRecord(\n        description=\"[history summary]\",\n        tool=\"_summary\",\n        tool_input={},\n        result=summary_text,\n    )\n    return [summary_step] + recent\n"
          }
        ]
      },
